		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Military Commissions Act of 2006</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">"HR6166" redirects here. For the star (H Sco), see <a href="/wiki/List_of_stars_in_Scorpius" title="List of stars in Scorpius">List of stars in Scorpius</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:322px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Bush_signing_Military_Commissions_Act_of_2006.jpg" class="image" title="President George W. Bush signs into law S. 3930, the Military Commissions Act of 2006, during a ceremony on October 17, 2006 in the East Room of the White House."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/Bush_signing_Military_Commissions_Act_of_2006.jpg/320px-Bush_signing_Military_Commissions_Act_of_2006.jpg" width="320" height="249" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Bush_signing_Military_Commissions_Act_of_2006.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
President <a href="/wiki/George_W._Bush" title="George W. Bush">George W. Bush</a> signs into law S. 3930, the Military Commissions Act of 2006, during a ceremony on October 17, 2006 in the <a href="/wiki/East_Room" title="East Room">East Room</a> of the <a href="/wiki/White_House" title="White House">White House</a>.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The United States <b>Military Commissions Act of 2006</b><sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>, also known as HR-6166, was an Act of Congress<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> signed by <a href="/wiki/President_of_the_United_States" title="President of the United States">President</a> <a href="/wiki/George_W._Bush" title="George W. Bush">George W. Bush</a> on October 17, 2006. Drafted in the wake of the <a href="/wiki/Supreme_Court_of_the_United_States" title="Supreme Court of the United States">Supreme Court</a>'s decision on <i><a href="/wiki/Hamdan_v._Rumsfeld" title="Hamdan v. Rumsfeld">Hamdan v. Rumsfeld</a></i>,<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> the Act's stated purpose was "To authorize trial by military commission for violations of the law of war, and for other purposes."<sup id="cite_ref-TheAct_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-TheAct-3" title=""><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Following the filing of <a href="/wiki/Al_Odah_v._United_States" title="Al Odah v. United States">Al Odah v. United States</a>, section 7 of the MCA was found to be unconstitutional by the <a href="/wiki/Supreme_Court_of_the_United_States" title="Supreme Court of the United States">Supreme Court</a> on June 12, 2008.<sup id="cite_ref-NYT_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-NYT-4" title=""><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
